WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.994 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.994 --> 00:00:03.976 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.976 --> 00:00:19.890 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.890 --> 00:00:25.310 align:middle line:10%
>> Is it possible to really
have happiness in this life?

00:00:25.310 --> 00:00:26.930 align:middle line:10%
Well, we have some
help for you if you

00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:28.730 align:middle line:10%
think you'd like to try it.

00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:32.780 align:middle line:84%
We have Dr. Robert Thurman
who has written a book called

00:00:32.780 --> 00:00:34.430 align:middle line:90%
"Inner Revolution--

00:00:34.430 --> 00:00:38.210 align:middle line:84%
Life, Liberty, and the
Pursuit of Real Happiness."

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.700 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Thurman is a internationally
recognized scholar.

00:00:43.700 --> 00:00:46.570 align:middle line:84%
He's a professor at
Columbia University.

00:00:46.570 --> 00:00:49.150 align:middle line:84%
He is an author and
he is a translator.

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:52.480 align:middle line:84%
And he was the first
American to have ever been

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:54.700 align:middle line:90%
ordained as a Buddhist monk.

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:55.743 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to "Wisdom."

00:00:55.743 --> 00:00:56.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, thank you, Corinne.

00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:58.935 align:middle line:84%
It's very nice to be here
with you this morning.

00:00:58.935 --> 00:01:03.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, I think it's important
to start off by not thinking

00:01:03.580 --> 00:01:07.130 align:middle line:84%
that everybody knows
what Buddhism is.

00:01:07.130 --> 00:01:10.170 align:middle line:84%
And, in particular,
who was Buddha?

00:01:10.170 --> 00:01:11.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:13.350 align:middle line:10%
Well, I think you're
right, Corinne.

00:01:13.350 --> 00:01:15.820 align:middle line:10%
Buddha was a prince trained--

00:01:15.820 --> 00:01:18.270 align:middle line:10%
actually, he was like
a military cadet.

00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:20.880 align:middle line:84%
And he was a prince
trained to be a king.

00:01:20.880 --> 00:01:24.660 align:middle line:84%
And when he was 29, he decided
that there must be something

00:01:24.660 --> 00:01:26.880 align:middle line:84%
more to life than just
running his kingdom,

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:29.970 align:middle line:84%
having fun with his wife--
and wives, actually,

00:01:29.970 --> 00:01:31.480 align:middle line:90%
in that ancient time--

00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:33.660 align:middle line:90%
and then dying.

00:01:33.660 --> 00:01:35.330 align:middle line:84%
So he said I've
got to go and find

00:01:35.330 --> 00:01:37.110 align:middle line:90%
the higher meaning to things.

00:01:37.110 --> 00:01:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Or if there is none,
then I'll find that out.

00:01:39.450 --> 00:01:43.210 align:middle line:84%
And he took a vacation
at the age of 29.

00:01:43.210 --> 00:01:44.760 align:middle line:84%
And after six years
of meditating,

00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:49.740 align:middle line:84%
he said, wow, I really have
understood what it's all about.

00:01:49.740 --> 00:01:51.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm really glad I did this.

00:01:51.450 --> 00:01:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And I'm very happy to
announce that all of you

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:56.400 align:middle line:84%
can find out what it's all
about and that all of you

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:59.460 align:middle line:84%
can get away from this
sort of nagging anxiety

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:01.590 align:middle line:84%
and unpleasant time
that you're having.

00:02:01.590 --> 00:02:04.320 align:middle line:84%
And you can have real
happiness in this life

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:05.718 align:middle line:90%
and for all your future lives.

00:02:05.718 --> 00:02:07.260 align:middle line:84%
He made that kind
of an announcement.

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:08.060 align:middle line:90%
He was so happy.

00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:10.509 align:middle line:84%
He was euphoric,
actually, he was so happy.

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:12.120 align:middle line:84%
And then following
on that, Corinne,

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:16.200 align:middle line:84%
over the following 2,500
years in many countries,

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:19.410 align:middle line:84%
many people decided to
make use of those methods

00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:23.760 align:middle line:84%
to sort of get away from
the bad situation of feeling

00:02:23.760 --> 00:02:25.950 align:middle line:84%
separate from the universe,
feeling that you have

00:02:25.950 --> 00:02:27.660 align:middle line:84%
to fight with the
universe, and feeling

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:29.670 align:middle line:90%
that you're losing that fight.

00:02:29.670 --> 00:02:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And instead, they discovered
a way of becoming harmonious

00:02:32.370 --> 00:02:35.340 align:middle line:84%
with the universe and
really feel successful,

00:02:35.340 --> 00:02:39.410 align:middle line:84%
in a way, in your existence,
and attain nirvana, as they say,

00:02:39.410 --> 00:02:42.330 align:middle line:84%
the extinguishment
of this kind of

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:44.550 align:middle line:90%
unnecessary personal suffering.

00:02:44.550 --> 00:02:47.490 align:middle line:10%
And so many people were able
to do that that it became

00:02:47.490 --> 00:02:49.650 align:middle line:10%
a very vastly popular movement.

00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:51.780 align:middle line:84%
And it has the kind of
the reputation, Corinne,

00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:55.110 align:middle line:84%
of being a religion
by Westerners.

00:02:55.110 --> 00:02:56.370 align:middle line:90%
We think of it as a religion.

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:57.810 align:middle line:84%
It sort of fits
in our categories.

00:02:57.810 --> 00:03:00.372 align:middle line:84%
And it can, to some
degree, be a religion.

00:03:00.372 --> 00:03:01.830 align:middle line:84%
But from the Buddha's
point of view

00:03:01.830 --> 00:03:03.900 align:middle line:84%
and the major
teachers of Buddhism,

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:06.570 align:middle line:84%
it's thought of more as
a system of education,

00:03:06.570 --> 00:03:09.570 align:middle line:84%
how to reeducate yourself
not to have a miserable life

00:03:09.570 --> 00:03:12.280 align:middle line:84%
and, instead, have a
pleasant and happy life.

00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:15.520 align:middle line:84%
>> So you can be a jew and be a
Buddhist or follow the Buddhist

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:16.320 align:middle line:90%
teachings?

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:17.940 align:middle line:84%
>> It depends on
how you define it.

00:03:17.940 --> 00:03:21.120 align:middle line:84%
The way I define it, the way
the Dalai Lama defines it, yes,

00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:24.072 align:middle line:84%
you can be a Jew and
you can be a Buddhist.

00:03:24.072 --> 00:03:25.530 align:middle line:84%
The way someone
would define it who

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:27.000 align:middle line:84%
would think of it
as a religion, where

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:28.917 align:middle line:84%
you have to have a certain
credo and so forth,

00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:31.650 align:middle line:84%
then, no, you have to be
either a Jew or a Buddhist.

00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:35.100 align:middle line:84%
But even then, you can
use methods from Buddhism

00:03:35.100 --> 00:03:37.200 align:middle line:90%
and be a better Jew.

00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:38.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Or a better Catholic.

00:03:38.310 --> 00:03:40.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Or a better Catholic,
or a better Muslim,

00:03:40.320 --> 00:03:42.310 align:middle line:84%
or a better Hindu,
whatever it might be--

00:03:42.310 --> 00:03:43.200 align:middle line:90%
>> I remember a lot--

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:44.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Or a better
humanist, actually.

00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:47.250 align:middle line:84%
You know, you can be a
secular humanist in a way

00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:50.820 align:middle line:84%
and use methods from Buddhism
about moral, meditational, and

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:53.640 align:middle line:84%
intellectual methods,
psychological methods,

00:03:53.640 --> 00:03:56.550 align:middle line:84%
and you can be better at
whatever it is you do.

00:03:56.550 --> 00:03:59.610 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, almost every book
that comes past my desk these

00:03:59.610 --> 00:04:06.540 align:middle line:84%
days, it's either about Buddhism
or it is written by someone who

00:04:06.540 --> 00:04:08.880 align:middle line:84%
has learned something
from Buddhism.

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:11.210 align:middle line:90%
What is happening?

00:04:11.210 --> 00:04:12.510 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know.

00:04:12.510 --> 00:04:15.209 align:middle line:84%
It's coming out of
the woodwork, I guess.

00:04:15.209 --> 00:04:16.709 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know,
Arnold Toynbee said,

00:04:16.709 --> 00:04:20.579 align:middle line:84%
Corinne, that the 20th
century in later--

00:04:20.579 --> 00:04:24.008 align:middle line:84%
25th century historians looking
back at the 20th century,

00:04:24.008 --> 00:04:25.800 align:middle line:84%
they would say that
the greatest thing that

00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:28.830 align:middle line:84%
happened in the 20th century was
not the telephone, the TV, what

00:04:28.830 --> 00:04:33.360 align:middle line:84%
have you, it was the encounter
by the Western EuroAmerican

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:36.750 align:middle line:84%
culture with Buddhism
from Asia that

00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:39.900 align:middle line:84%
would be the greatest event
that would mark the succeeding

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:41.250 align:middle line:90%
number of centuries.

00:04:41.250 --> 00:04:44.940 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people might be
very paranoid about that idea,

00:04:44.940 --> 00:04:48.820 align:middle line:84%
particularly Christians, or
some orthodox Jews, in that they

00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:50.820 align:middle line:84%
would think that, oh,
dear, that means we're all

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:53.080 align:middle line:84%
going to somehow supposed
to convert to this religion,

00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:53.880 align:middle line:90%
you see.

00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:56.047 align:middle line:84%
Which is why I think it's
very important to get away

00:04:56.047 --> 00:04:57.930 align:middle line:84%
from the idea that
it's just a religion.

00:04:57.930 --> 00:05:01.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean I teach about Buddhism
in a university in a department

00:05:01.590 --> 00:05:04.230 align:middle line:84%
of religion, because
people are thinking

00:05:04.230 --> 00:05:06.670 align:middle line:84%
that it was some sort
of belief system,

00:05:06.670 --> 00:05:08.370 align:middle line:84%
which is how
religion is defined,

00:05:08.370 --> 00:05:09.703 align:middle line:90%
that is used in Asian countries.

00:05:09.703 --> 00:05:10.578 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean?

00:05:10.578 --> 00:05:12.750 align:middle line:84%
So I teach the history
and what they do there.

00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:16.200 align:middle line:84%
But really, I should be teaching
in a philosophy department,

00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:19.622 align:middle line:84%
or a psychology department,
or some sort of human science

00:05:19.622 --> 00:05:21.330 align:middle line:84%
department really
rather than a religion.

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:23.640 align:middle line:84%
Because really
what Buddhism is is

00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:26.790 align:middle line:84%
the science of the human
mind, the human emotions,

00:05:26.790 --> 00:05:27.930 align:middle line:90%
how they work.

00:05:27.930 --> 00:05:31.050 align:middle line:84%
It relates also to biology, to
medicine, to many other things.

00:05:31.050 --> 00:05:32.840 align:middle line:90%
And it really is a science.

00:05:32.840 --> 00:05:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, the reason I think it's
becoming so well known now

00:05:35.730 --> 00:05:38.940 align:middle line:84%
in America is that, I think,
we are a little discouraged

00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:42.300 align:middle line:84%
with our own native
psychology, which really

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:46.260 align:middle line:84%
is very constrained by its
philosophy of materialism

00:05:46.260 --> 00:05:48.240 align:middle line:90%
and really boils down to Prozac.

00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:51.060 align:middle line:84%
Take some sort of a chemical
that will alter your mood

00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:52.883 align:middle line:84%
and that's supposed
to solve your problem.

00:05:52.883 --> 00:05:54.300 align:middle line:84%
The insurance
companies won't even

00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:57.420 align:middle line:84%
pay for you to go and talk
to a therapist anymore,

00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:59.790 align:middle line:84%
because they've sort of
given up on people's having

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:02.040 align:middle line:90%
a soul and et cetera, you know?

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:05.880 align:middle line:84%
So our psychology runs counter
to our moral and religious

00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:07.020 align:middle line:90%
imperatives.

00:06:07.020 --> 00:06:09.810 align:middle line:84%
And the moral and religious ones
tell you you should be moral,

00:06:09.810 --> 00:06:12.650 align:middle line:84%
you should be kind, you
shouldn't be too selfish.

00:06:12.650 --> 00:06:14.650 align:middle line:84%
And the psychologist says
you should be selfish,

00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:16.817 align:middle line:84%
you should have a big ego,
and you should run around

00:06:16.817 --> 00:06:17.640 align:middle line:90%
to be aggressive.

00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:20.810 align:middle line:84%
And both of them seem
sort of too extreme.

00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:23.130 align:middle line:84%
And in the middle of that,
Buddhism comes along.

00:06:23.130 --> 00:06:26.610 align:middle line:84%
And it gives us a
practical method

00:06:26.610 --> 00:06:29.790 align:middle line:84%
of how we can be less selfish,
and more moral, and more

00:06:29.790 --> 00:06:33.270 align:middle line:84%
happy as a psychological
necessity, not just

00:06:33.270 --> 00:06:36.480 align:middle line:84%
as a sort of a way of
behaving, if you follow me.

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:37.890 align:middle line:90%
>> How do we do that, Bob?

00:06:37.890 --> 00:06:40.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the main thing
we have to do, Corinne,

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:43.110 align:middle line:84%
the main thing that is the inner
revolution that I write about

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:47.840 align:middle line:84%
in my "Inner Revolution" book
is we have to turn around from

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:51.410 align:middle line:84%
being self-obsessed and
perceiving the world only from

00:06:51.410 --> 00:06:54.680 align:middle line:84%
our own perspective where we
think that everything revolves

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:55.610 align:middle line:90%
around me.

00:06:55.610 --> 00:06:56.900 align:middle line:90%
I should have everything.

00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And no one should
do anything to me.

00:06:58.400 --> 00:06:59.930 align:middle line:90%
I don't want this kind of thing.

00:06:59.930 --> 00:07:02.457 align:middle line:84%
And once I'm in
that frame of mind,

00:07:02.457 --> 00:07:04.040 align:middle line:84%
what the Buddha
discovered is once I'm

00:07:04.040 --> 00:07:06.320 align:middle line:90%
in a frame of mind like that--

00:07:06.320 --> 00:07:09.020 align:middle line:84%
which some people think is
only natural or inevitable that

00:07:09.020 --> 00:07:10.640 align:middle line:90%
everyone automatically is--

00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:12.560 align:middle line:84%
but he discovered that
that frame of mind

00:07:12.560 --> 00:07:14.100 align:middle line:90%
leads to suffering inevitably.

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:14.900 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:19.850 align:middle line:84%
Because the universe is not
going to be swallowed by me.

00:07:19.850 --> 00:07:22.290 align:middle line:84%
The universe is not going
to do what I want it to do.

00:07:22.290 --> 00:07:23.750 align:middle line:84%
And so when I think
it should, I'm

00:07:23.750 --> 00:07:25.580 align:middle line:84%
going to be always
in conflict with it.

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:27.080 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to
lose that conflict.

00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:27.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to die.

00:07:27.880 --> 00:07:29.150 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to get sick.

00:07:29.150 --> 00:07:30.680 align:middle line:90%
Friends are going to leave me.

00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:32.670 align:middle line:84%
Enemies are going
to come up to me.

00:07:32.670 --> 00:07:36.170 align:middle line:84%
And so as long as I think that
it should revolve around me,

00:07:36.170 --> 00:07:37.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to be in
stress because I'm

00:07:37.910 --> 00:07:39.960 align:middle line:84%
going to be out of
touch with reality.

00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:42.350 align:middle line:84%
If I can shift
that over, not just

00:07:42.350 --> 00:07:44.690 align:middle line:84%
on the basis of a kind
of an act of willpower,

00:07:44.690 --> 00:07:46.550 align:middle line:84%
but on the basis
of understanding

00:07:46.550 --> 00:07:49.700 align:middle line:84%
the salaciousness, the
erroneousness of thinking

00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:52.070 align:middle line:84%
that I'm so special,
do you follow me?

00:07:52.070 --> 00:07:55.010 align:middle line:84%
And realize it's not
that I don't exist

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:56.723 align:middle line:84%
or that I'm not
special, it's just

00:07:56.723 --> 00:07:58.640 align:middle line:84%
that I'm no more special
than everything else.

00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:00.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm interactive
with other things.

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:03.770 align:middle line:84%
And I exist relatively and
relationally with other things.

00:08:03.770 --> 00:08:06.292 align:middle line:84%
When I really viscerally
understand that, Corinne,

00:08:06.292 --> 00:08:08.750 align:middle line:84%
you see suddenly my relationship
with everything completely

00:08:08.750 --> 00:08:09.680 align:middle line:90%
changes.

00:08:09.680 --> 00:08:12.260 align:middle line:84%
And things are rewarding
to me and friendly to me.

00:08:12.260 --> 00:08:14.730 align:middle line:84%
And I can be happy with
them instead of in conflict

00:08:14.730 --> 00:08:15.530 align:middle line:90%
with them.

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:16.400 align:middle line:90%
Do you follow me?

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.080 align:middle line:84%
In other words, say
you and I, Corinne,

00:08:18.080 --> 00:08:19.740 align:middle line:90%
are two different people.

00:08:19.740 --> 00:08:22.520 align:middle line:10%
If I think somehow
my well-being depends

00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:25.610 align:middle line:10%
on kind of suppressing you or
doing something against you,

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:28.220 align:middle line:10%
you and I will be in
stress all the time.

00:08:28.220 --> 00:08:30.434 align:middle line:84%
But if I feel, well,
you and I are connected.

00:08:30.434 --> 00:08:32.059 align:middle line:84%
And actually, if
you're in a good mood,

00:08:32.059 --> 00:08:34.348 align:middle line:84%
and cheery, and happy,
that improves my mood.

00:08:34.348 --> 00:08:36.140 align:middle line:84%
If you get something
out of whatever it is,

00:08:36.140 --> 00:08:37.549 align:middle line:90%
I get something out of it.

00:08:37.549 --> 00:08:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And we're more
exchanging like that,

00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:41.630 align:middle line:84%
then I'm not in
conflict with you.

00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:43.460 align:middle line:84%
Then, in fact,
enhancing your situation

00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:44.990 align:middle line:90%
enhances my situation.

00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>> But you go on at great length
in your book "Inner Revolution"

00:08:48.860 --> 00:08:52.220 align:middle line:84%
about how people have to get
away from the community and get

00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:55.790 align:middle line:84%
back to the individual and the
education of the individual.

00:08:55.790 --> 00:08:58.207 align:middle line:84%
That kind of runs counter
to what you're just saying.

00:08:58.207 --> 00:08:59.040 align:middle line:90%
>> That's very good.

00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:02.000 align:middle line:84%
In a way, it seems to at
first, you're correct.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:04.400 align:middle line:84%
But the reason being
that, normally,

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:06.170 align:middle line:84%
in many, many
communities-- like, say,

00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:08.960 align:middle line:84%
a communist society or
an ancient society that

00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:11.120 align:middle line:84%
is what we call a
very collectivistic,

00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:12.890 align:middle line:84%
that is to say the
individual is meant

00:09:12.890 --> 00:09:15.440 align:middle line:84%
to submerge their
self-interest in life

00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:19.370 align:middle line:84%
very much under some
duties to the community.

00:09:19.370 --> 00:09:21.860 align:middle line:84%
Under that situation,
you see, the person

00:09:21.860 --> 00:09:23.570 align:middle line:84%
is still really feeling
that they should

00:09:23.570 --> 00:09:25.130 align:middle line:90%
be the center of the universe.

00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And then they're
suppressing that feeling

00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:30.230 align:middle line:84%
and doing something for the
community under pressure.

00:09:30.230 --> 00:09:33.280 align:middle line:84%
And then that only adds to
their sense of unhappiness,

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:34.460 align:middle line:90%
do you follow me?

00:09:34.460 --> 00:09:36.470 align:middle line:84%
So why I say, ancient
Indian society

00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:39.860 align:middle line:84%
based on Buddha's insight was
more individualistic, actually,

00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:41.540 align:middle line:90%
than America or any place.

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:43.820 align:middle line:84%
Because what it said
was human beings

00:09:43.820 --> 00:09:47.450 align:middle line:84%
are such an amazing,
evolutionary phenomenon

00:09:47.450 --> 00:09:49.070 align:middle line:84%
that they should
use that human life

00:09:49.070 --> 00:09:52.220 align:middle line:84%
to come to a realistic
understanding of themselves.

00:09:52.220 --> 00:09:55.010 align:middle line:10%
And once they do, then they
can contribute far more

00:09:55.010 --> 00:09:58.640 align:middle line:10%
to any community than they
possibly could being miserable,

00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:01.580 align:middle line:10%
and suppressed, and coerced.

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:03.440 align:middle line:10%
So therefore, an
intelligent society

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.330 align:middle line:10%
releases its
individuals as much as

00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:08.150 align:middle line:10%
possible to come to their
own self-understanding

00:10:08.150 --> 00:10:10.430 align:middle line:10%
and fulfillment,
because it knows

00:10:10.430 --> 00:10:13.220 align:middle line:10%
that once they're educated,
and once they really understand

00:10:13.220 --> 00:10:15.050 align:middle line:10%
their relationship
with the universe,

00:10:15.050 --> 00:10:18.710 align:middle line:10%
they will make so much greater
a contribution voluntarily

00:10:18.710 --> 00:10:21.050 align:middle line:10%
and willingly to the
community than they ever

00:10:21.050 --> 00:10:24.530 align:middle line:10%
would have as just a coerced
slave of some sort of community

00:10:24.530 --> 00:10:25.910 align:middle line:10%
duty.

00:10:25.910 --> 00:10:27.920 align:middle line:84%
So that's the paradox
in there, Corinne.

00:10:27.920 --> 00:10:30.590 align:middle line:84%
First, you need to let the
person have plenty of room

00:10:30.590 --> 00:10:32.550 align:middle line:90%
